<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property">
  A <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> specifies text based
properties of a  
  <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.   
  <example number="1">
    The character code, such as 'EBCDIC', used in the document.
  </example>

  <p>
    When the <b>Document_descriptive_property</b> is applied to a 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Digital_document_definition"/>
    through the <b>described_element</b> attribute, the
    <b>Document_descriptive_property</b> applies to all 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>s
    that are components of the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Digital_document_definition"/>.
  </p>

  <p>
    When the <b>Document_descriptive_property</b> is applied to a 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Physical_document_definition"/>
    through the <b>described_element</b> attribute, the
    <b>Document_descriptive_property</b> applies to all 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Hardcopy"/>s
    that are components of the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Physical_document_definition"/>.
  </p>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: property_type 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_type">
  The <b>property_type</b> attribute identifies the category to which the
  property belongs.
  <p>
    Where applicable, the following categories shall be used:    
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
    'Document content property': a category of properties that
    detail the content of a given 
    <express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
    <p>
      The following names are 
      <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
      that are categorized as 'Document content property':
        <note>
          The names are stored in the <b>property_name</b> attribute of
        the <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>.
        </note>
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        'detail level': the level of detail that the 
        <express_ref 
          linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
        provides.
        <example number="1">
          'rough 3d shape': 3D shape model without edge rounds and fillets.
        </example>
      </li>
      <li>
        'geometry_type': the kind or kinds of geometry that an object
        contains. 
        <example number="2">
          '3D wireframe model': The document contains a 3D shape model in
          wireframe representation;  
        </example>
      </li>
      <li>
        'languages':
        The languages specifies which language or languages are used in the
        characterized objects.  
        <example number="3">
          'Japanese' and 'German' are examples for the fact that annotation
          on a drawing is provided in the language 'Japanese' or 'German'
          respectively.  
        </example>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </li>

    <li>
      'Document creation property': a category of properties that detail
      the context of creation of a <express_ref linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. 
    <p>
      The following names are 
      <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
      that are categorized as 'Document creation property':
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        'creating_system': 
        The creating_system specifies the computer application or the machine
        which is used to create the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
      </li>
      <li>
        'creating_interface':
        The creating_interface specifies the computer application used to
        create the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.       
        <example number="4">
          'Postscript Printer Driver' is an example for a creating interface
          of a Physical_document.
        </example>
      </li>
      <li>
        'operating_system':
        The operating_system specifies the operating system that is used to
        execute the computer application that created the
        
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. 
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p/>
  </li>
  <li>
    'Document format property': a category of properties that describe
    the format of a 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.

    <p>
      The following names are 
      <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
      that are categorized as 'Document format property':
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        'data_format':
        The data_format specifies the convention that was used to structure
        the information in the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
      <example number="5">
        'ISO 10303-203' is an example of a data format indicating that the
        document contains data in ISO 10303-203 format.
      </example>
      </li>

      <li>
        'character_code':
        The character_code specifies the character code that is used in the
        
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
        <example number="6">
          'binary' is an example of a character code
          indicating that the document contains data in binary format;         
        </example>
      </li>

   <li>
     'size_format':
     The size_format specifies the dimensions of a physical presentation of
     the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
     <example number="7">
       'ISO A0' is an example for the size_format of a drawing that is
       stored digitally.
     </example>
   </li>

    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: property_name 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_name">
  The property_name specifies the name of the
  <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> that is assigned to the
  <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
  <example>
    'size_format' is a name given to the <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
     that specifies the dimensions of a physical presentation of
     the 
<express_ref
  linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
  </example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: property_value 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_value">
The property_value is the descriptive text that applies to the <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: described_element 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.described_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.described_element">
  The described_element is the 
     <express_ref
       linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
     to which the <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> is assigned.
</ext_description>

